The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Sunday, May 23, 2004 				Metro Recommends
THE VCD 
	(Angel Video) This Ray classic, which won the national award in 1958 and the best music award at the Moscow Film Festival the following year, has now been released on view CD. Based on a story by Tarashankar Bandopadhyay and directed and scripted by the maestro himself, the film is anchored by a powerful performance by Chhabi Biswas. Subrata Mitras cinematography and Ustad Vilayat Khans music add to the atmosphere. THE BOOK
	(Jerry Pinto amp; Naresh Fernandes) A compilation of poems and prose pieces by well-known writers, in addition to cartoons, photographs, a song and even the Bombay Duck recipe, the book is a toast to the spirit of the metropolisTHE FILM FEST				 																																	(Gorky Sadan, May 26-June 6, 6 pm) Organised by Eisenstein Cine Club, the festival brings together seven films on a wide spectrum of subjects  from the intense Desh (picture below) to the sci-fi Patalghar to the true-to-tradition Bagh Bahadur 

